Quote: SITE OF THE NEW TOWNSHIP ON THE HOGBURN.        A deputation from the storekeepers and miners on the Hogburn rush waited on his Honor the Superintendent yesterday, to present a memorial, praying the Government to take steps to rescind the order issued by the Crown Lands Ranger, to remove the stores from their present site to the new township lately marked out by the Warden, Mr Hardcastle.
